# supercronic crontab for apiV2 — consumed by the `sync-cron` service in
# docker-compose.yml. Copied into the image at /app/deploy/crontab.
#
# Scheduling rationale:
#   * Every 15 min → `reindex incremental`
#       Fast delta push: only rows whose `updated_at` advanced past the
#       Redis-stored watermark (`sync:jobs:watermark`).
#   * Every day at 03:00 → `reindex full`
#       Safety net against drift: rebuilds the Meilisearch index from
#       Postgres, wipes and re-pushes every row.
#
# Overlap safety:
#   Both commands call into app/sync/runner.py, which advisory-locks
#   the Redis key `sync:jobs:lock` (TTL = SYNC_LOCK_TTL seconds, default
#   3600). If the one-shot `sync-init` (run on every Coolify deploy) is
#   still working when a scheduled tick fires, the tick short-circuits
#   with a `sync.*.lock_held` log line and exits 0 — no contention, no
#   duplicate writes.
#
# Timezone:
#   supercronic interprets schedules in the container's local time.
#   Keep the container on UTC (default for the python:3.13-slim base
#   image) unless you set TZ in the compose env.
#
# Format reminder (m h dom mon dow):
#   *    *    *    *    *    command
#   │    │    │    │    └── day-of-week (0–7, 0 & 7 = Sun)
#   │    │    │    └────── month (1–12)
#   │    │    └─────────── day-of-month (1–31)
#   │    └──────────────── hour (0–23)
#   └───────────────────── minute (0–59)

*/15 * * * * /app/.venv/bin/python -m app.sync.cli reindex incremental
0   3 * * * /app/.venv/bin/python -m app.sync.cli reindex full
